climbs.name: Window Crack
climbs.fa: Pete VanSlooten, Nate Brown, Tyler Phillips

content.description: The crux very well may be pulling up into the window itself.Good jams, good gear make this one hard to pass up.
content.protection: You start the route w/ a #1 camalot followed by a #2 camalot followed by a #3 camalot. Pretty weird huh?
content.location: If you cannot find this route, well, look at the name, then look around you, it's the only route with a window.

climbs.name: Sink the Pink
climbs.fa: Tyler Phillips, Pete the Meat, Nate Brown, Nate Williams, Brenden Brinkley

content.description:
The crux is right off the ground pulling yourself over the mini roof with tight hands. But can you say splitter?

The name was derived from the peanut gallery shouting to sink the #1.5 friend that had a pink sling on it at the time.
content.protection: A single set 'o' cams should do.
content.location: This is the back of AC/DC crack, the crack splits the formation with AC/DC on the front and Sink the Pink on the back. Descend from communal anchors on Window Crack.

content.description: Great aesthetic line that goes right up the middle of a great rock.  First you're pulling a sequence of positive two-finger pockets (V4 crux) followed by some jugs with some big moves.  Overall great sequences on great rock.
content.location: When facing Widow Rock, it is the sport route that goes right up the middle of the left face.

climbs.name: AC/DC Crack
climbs.fa: Tyler Phillips, Pete the Meat, Nate Brown

content.description: This ever widening crack offers up good holds just when you think you got to fist stack. Cool route that you can actully see light through from the other side if the lighting ias right
content.protection: Hand sizes and a big one (#4 camalot)
content.location: This route has the lighting bolt shape to it.It sits just to the right of Window Crack.
